    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Choosing Vanuatu Without Time Pressure</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Vanuatu's premium over Dominica (~$30K) is justified by speed. If you're not time-pressured, Caribbean programs offer more visa-free countries for less money. Only choose Vanuatu if speed actually matters for your situation.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Expecting US/Canada Visa-Free</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Vanuatu passport does NOT provide visa-free US or Canada access. If North America matters, you'll still need visas. For US access, Grenada (E-2 treaty) is the only Caribbean CBI option. Vanuatu is for UK/EU/Asia travel.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Planning to Actually Live in Vanuatu</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Vanuatu is beautiful but undeveloped. Population ~300,000, limited infrastructure, basic healthcare, cyclone risk. If you plan to actually reside there (vs holding passport), research extensively. Most CBI holders never visit.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Thinking Due Diligence is Lax</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Fast ≠ lax. Vanuatu conducts proper background checks through international agencies. Speed comes from streamlined administration, not skipped verification. Don't apply thinking you can hide issues.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Using Unlicensed Agents</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Vanuatu has fewer authorized agents than Caribbean programs. Some "agents" aren't actually licensed. Verify on official government website before engaging. Unlicensed facilitators cause problems.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
