  <!-- Section: FAQ -->
  <section id="faq" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Why is Vanuatu CBI so fast?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Smaller government with streamlined administration. Vanuatu processes fewer applications than Caribbean programs but has efficient systems. The country is motivated to maintain program integrity while delivering speed—it's a key selling point. Due diligence is still conducted properly.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Vanuatu passport respected?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Mixed reputation. It provides legitimate visa-free access to 112 countries including UK and EU (verified and functional). However, it's less established than Caribbean programs and has fewer visa-free destinations. Some countries scrutinize Vanuatu passports more closely. For UK/EU/Singapore travel, it works fine.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need to visit Vanuatu?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          No. The entire process is remote through your agent. You never need to visit—not for application, not for passport collection (shipped), not to maintain citizenship. No residency requirement. Most citizens never visit the islands.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's the tax situation?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Vanuatu has zero income tax, zero capital gains tax, zero wealth tax, and zero inheritance tax. This makes it attractive for tax planning. However, tax residency requires actually living there (which few do). Your tax obligations depend on where you actually reside, not your passport.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I use Vanuatu passport for US travel?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          No visa-free US access. Vanuatu citizens need US visa (B-1/B-2) for tourism/business visits. No E-2 treaty with US. If US access is important, consider Grenada instead (has E-2 treaty). Vanuatu is for UK/EU/Asia travel, not Americas.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How long does passport last?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Vanuatu passports are valid for 5 years (shorter than Caribbean 10-year passports). Renewable for life as citizen. Renewal requires application and fee (~$200). Plan for more frequent renewals compared to Caribbean options.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

